The paper deals with the inapproximability of a graph problem and its applications in various areas such as bioinformatics, machine learning, and databases. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories such as cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.IT (Information Theory). However, since the paper focuses on the computational complexity of the problem and its inapproximability, cs.CC and cs.DS are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves graph theory and optimization, which are relevant to cs.DM. The applications in bioinformatics and machine learning suggest cs.LG, while the use of information theory in one of the applications suggests cs.IT.
